This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object detection, segmentation, and pose estimation, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to learn a mixture of compositional models, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper incorporates semantic cues, which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimodal learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to efficiently perform inference, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
